"{\"description\":\"Technician role in Sittingbourne, GB Department, providing essential link between Team Leader and team's Operatives, specialising in Track maintenance, inspection, and repair. Working in all weathers, outdoors, and embracing a changing shift pattern including days, nights, and weekends. Essential criteria include organizing safe systems of work, strong communication skills, willingness to work shifts in all weathers, and meeting the required benchmark for application screening questions. Salary \\tï¿½34,244. Closing date: 17th November 2023. Recruitment process is a Competency based interview.\",\"howToApply\":\"To apply for this role, click 'apply now'. Network Rail is dedicated to creating an inclusive environment and welcomes applications from everyone. Network Rail is a Disability Confident Leader and will try its best to adapt the process and offer a reasonable alternative to help support people with disabilities access, apply, and interview for roles. All offers of employment are conditional upon satisfactory completion of pre-employment checks such as drugs and alcohol test.\",\"aboutTheRole\":{\"essential\":[\"Sittingbourne, GB\",\"Track maintenance, inspection, and repair\",\"Organizing safe systems of work\",\"Strong communication skills\",\"Willingness to work shifts in all weathers\"],\"desirable\":[],\"keyAccountabilities\":[\"Providing essential link between Team Leader and team's Operatives\",\"Specializing in Track maintenance, inspection, and repair\",\"Working outdoors in all weathers, day or night, and transport kit across tricky terrain\",\"Leading the team when asked by the team leader\",\"Promoting safe working behaviours and challenging potential risks\",\"Commitment to self-development and continuous learning\",\"Holding an NVQ Level 1 or 2 linked to the discipline or equivalent experience\"]}}"